node.text:
Developing a new tool and putting the prototype through the ringer! 💪 

This is something that I encourage my students to do if they want to practice the cut across the bottom of the bowl- chuck up a piece of wood and go straight to that cut- but add some distance between the tool rest and the wood to make it realistic. 

When a piano player wants to perfect a certain few measures, they practice those few measures until it sounds right. Why play the entire song every time if you’re only trying to improve one part? 

📸 by @evanlaettner

node.text:
The day 9 years ago when, before the Farmers Market, Turner showed up at my house with a collar and no tags. She looked like she had been running all night. I decided to bring her, and she decided she didn’t mind. 

She had a chip that put me in touch with a woman who had lost her three years before. Through social media, that lady found the second owner and decided to give her back. Three weeks after that, I got a call from the first owner saying Turner kept running away and still had no tags. She gave my number to the guy who had her, and she’s lived with me ever since. 

Today we’re on our way to emergency care for her. She’s scheduled for surgery on Tuesday, but it doesn’t look like she can wait. Please send her some positivity. ❤️

#fbf #turner #girlsbestfriend #sweetgirl
